column1: Baby Barnaby's////The one time I tried something else
column2: it was the seasonal fruit pancake. I believe my fruit was the banana walnut. When the menu says "pancake" in the singular form
column3: it means it. You only get one pancake. One giant pancake. One giant pancake the size of a hubcap. At first I rather enjoyed my banana walnut hubcap pancake -- it was fluffy and packed with barely warmed-through bananas and soft walnuts. But by the 30th bite
column4: I was over it. I imagine this is what that guy from Man Vs. Food feels when he has to chew through a six-pound burrito. Maybe if I had someone (or somethree) to share it with
column5: it would've been more enjoyable. Lesson learned.
